## What is Enhancer?
**Enhancer** is a package of features that improve the base game experience without adding new dimensions, bosses, armor and weapon sets, or mobs. Almost all additions are created to give extra uses to existing, near-useless items. 

It also includes a lot of **generation** changes and a bit of **rebalancing**. The mod is made to feel and look like vanilla; for when you want something new, but don't want to spend a dozen hours on a wiki.

This mod also works as an addition to nearly any modpack: it doesn't conflict with anything, nor is it 'invasive': If you don't want to look for features from the mod, they're never shoved in your face. Below is a complete list of additions and changes the mod introduces; for further details, see the **changelog**.

## **New Blocks:**
* Added 4 new wild versions of existing crops naturally generating in the world:
  * **Sea Beet**: grows on Gravel, Sand, Stone and Coarse Dirt near water;
  * **Wheatgrass**: grows in Plains;
  * **Wild Carrot**: grows in non-Flower Forests;
  * **Wild Potato**: grows in Savannas and Swamps;
* Added **Reinforced Stone** and **Reinforced Deepslate**. Inherit all properties of their regular versions, but are blast resistant. Crafted using Copper.
* Added **Rockcress**, a flower bed block growing on Cobblestone and Mossy Cobblestone in Old Growth Birch Forests;
* Added **Infused Quartz Block**, crafted with Lapis and Quartz Blocks. Can be used as a **Beacon Base**;
* Added **Andesite, Diorite and Granite Tiles**, crafted from Polished blocks on a Stonecutter;
* Added **Paper Walls**, a new Wall type crafted with Paper and Sticks.

## **New Foods:**
* Added 9 new Food types, with potion effects:
  * Nether Fungi Stew;
  * Glow Salad;
  * Sea Dinner;
  * Fish Salad;
  * Sweet Berry Jam;
  * Sweet Berry Pie;
  * Honey Pancake;
  * Melon Juice;
  * Golden Delight.

## New Potions:
* **Potion of the Blind Guardian** - is brewed using Echo Shards on a Mundane Potion;
* **Potion of the Roaring Star** - is brewed using Nether Star on a Thick Potion.

## **New Structures:**
* Added 8 new Structures to the Overworld, some containing chests with unique loot tables:
  * **Plains Ruins** (4 variants): generate in Plains; 
  * **Desert Ruins** (4 variants): generate in Deserts;
  * **Stellas** (8 variants): generate in non-Cold Mountains and on Hills;
  * **Overgrown Stellas** (3 variants): generate in Cherry Groves;
  * **Tree Rings** (3 variants): generate in Forests;
  * **Cold Ruins** (3 variants): generate in snowy biomes;
  * **Savanna Trail Ruins** (Jigsaw): generate in savanna biomes;
  * **Badlands Outpost** (Jigsaw): generates in the Badlands;
## **New Advancements:**
* **World of Goo**: smelt a Lily Pad;
* **See Sights**: visit every new Structure.
## Fertilizer:
* Added **Fertilizer**, Crafted with Algae and either Rotten Flesh or Bone Meal;
* Using Fertilizer on a Farmland will turn it into a **Fertilized Farmland**;
* Added **Fertilized Farmland**:
  * Crops grow slightly faster;
  * Can get moisuture from 8 blocks horizontally and 2 blocks vertically, instead of 4 and 0;
  * Can't be trampled;
  * Even if left without water, will never turn to Dirt naturally;
  * When destroyed, will drop 1 Dirt block and 0-2 Algae.
## **Vanilla Tweaks:**
* Potions can be stacked up to 16;
* Books are no longer enchantable. Now, to enchant a Book, you need to craft an Amethyst Book first;
* Added Amethyst Book;
* Added crafting recipe for Experience Bottles using Echo Shards;
* Added **Algae**, obtained by smelting Lily Pads. Can be used as a Fuel, as well as a substitude for some Slime Ball and Coal recipes;


### Birch Forest:
* Old Growth Birch Forests now generate Forest Rocks, like other Old Growth biomes do;
* Tall Grass and Lily Pads now generate here, as well as Rockcress;
* A non-Mossy Cobblestone rock might generate instead of a regular one. Those have a chance of having a block of Raw Iron inside.

### **Food Changes:**
  * Balanced Died Advancement was updated to include the new food types;
  * Changed crafting recipes for Beetroot Soup, Pumpkin Pie and Cookies;
  * Cookies can now be eaten faster;

  * Changed effects gained from eating the following:
    * Beetroot Soup;
    * Rabbit Stew;
    * Pumpkin Pie;
    * Cookies.

### **Furnaces**
* Ancient Debris now smelt 4 times slower in the regular Furnace;

* Blast Furnace is changed to Enhanced Blast Furnace, a direct upgrade to a regular Furnace smelting any item at twice the speed. Crafted using Copper.

* Raw Ore blocks can be smelted in the Enhanced Blast Furnace, taking time of 8 regular items. This makes it the most efficient way of smelting huge amounts of Raw Ore;

* Rails and Chains can be smelted into Iron Nuggets;

* Music Discs Otherside, Pigstep, Relic and 5 can now be smelted into resources and XP in the Enhanced Blast Furnace.

### **Stonecutter**
* Renamed to 'Table Saw';
* In addition to its old functions, now also works on every type of Planks, Wood and Logs;
  * Planks -> 2 Slabs or 1 Stairs;
  * Wood -> Log;
  * Log -> Stripped Log;
  * Bamboo Block -> 9 Bamboo;
* Now requires Reinforced Stone to craft.


### **Loot Tables:**
  * Wheat Seeds are no longer dropped by any type of Grass;
  * Strays now have a chance of dropping Packed Ice;
  * Husks now have a chance of dropping Sand.
  * Zombie Villagers now are much more likely to drop Crops.

### **Other:**
  * Rotten Flesh, Poisonous Potatoes and Spider Eyes are now composterable;
  * Andesite, Diorite, Granite and Tuff can now be used in most Cobblestone recipes;
  * Redstone components using Cobblestone as a crafting material can now use any of the following as a replacement:
    * Cobbled Deepslate,
    * Blackstone,
    * Andesite,
    * Diorite,
    * Granite,
    * Tuff;
  * Slime Balls can be used to craft Torches.
